Steps to Set Up and Test the Contact Form

Step 1: Set Up Your Local Web Server

-> Download and Install XAMPP/WAMP/MAMP:
XAMPP: Download XAMPP

-> Start the Web Server:
XAMPP: Open XAMPP Control Panel and start the Apache server.

-> Place Your HTML File in the Server Directory:
XAMPP: Copy Contact.html to the htdocs directory (e.g., C:\xampp\htdocs\your-project).


Step 2: First Test - Activating the Form
-> Open the Contact Page:
Open your web browser and navigate to http://localhost/your-project (replace your-project with the appropriate directory name).

-> Submit Test Values:
Fill out the form with test values and click "Send Message".

-> Activate the Form:
Check the inbox of the target email address (dementor.help@gmail.com) for an activation email from FormSubmit.
Follow the instructions in the email to activate the form.

Step 3: Second Test - Verifying Email Delivery
-> Submit Dummy Values:
After activating the form, go back to the contact page.
Enter dummy values in the form and click "Send Message".

-> Check Email Delivery:
Check the inbox of the target email address (dementor.help@gmail.com) to verify that the form submission details have been received.

For more reference, you can watch this video tutorial: https://youtu.be/iSobU_DjNN4?si=GXnZuIdxctLvygKs
